hors develop afro-epistemologies grounded in Caribbean feminist spiritualities and manifest a commitment to finding joy and love in difference. Literary, anthropological, and more, Feminist Spiritualities weaves through a series of fields and methodologies in an undisciplined way to contribute new close readings of recent works and fresh assessments of well-known ones.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminism in literature. 0aFeminismzCaribbean Area. 0aWomen authors, CaribbeanxHistory and criticism. 4aAfrican American Studies : Black Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Caribbean Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Spirituality. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849342840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493428/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles